accessibility.text: The red warrior, Mars, with its rusty landscapes and colossal volcanoes, beckons us with the promise of adventure and discovery.
Venus, the dazzling morning star, is shrouded in sulfuric acid clouds. Its surface is scorching hot with crushing pressures.
Our blue oasis, Earth, teems with life and vibrant ecosystems, making it the only known planet to harbor life.
The swift messenger, Mercury, races around the Sun in just 88 days, with searing heat by day and freezing cold by night.
